<Content>Decent for business, OK for vacation I spent a weekend at the Hotel Conrad Miami for a conference. First, the location. The hotel is located in downtown Miami, in the financial district. If you're here on business, that's fine. However, all the fun is in South Beach, which is a good 15-20 minute cab ride away, which costs $25-$30. This is where the good restaurants, night clubs, and beaches are.We all found the check in very odd. It is on the 25th floor. From there, you need to take a 2nd elevator to get to your room. So, to get to the gym, or to leave the building, you need to take 2 elevators, which can be an annoyance. The bar and restaurant are on this floor, and I didn't try either.The room itself was beautiful. Nice marble countertops, and a well designed bathroom. The only problem with the room was that the TV was pretty small. For a hotel of this quality and a large room, I was expecting a better TV.The hotel gym is decent. It is under construction, so it probably will be in better shape. The exercise equipment is modern, with each cardio machine having its own TV set. I did not visit the adjacent spa.All in all, it's a nice business hotel. However, for vacationers, there really is no reason to stay here, and I would head to south beach, and get a hotel there. 
