<Content>A great hotel experience... We stayed at the Conrad between 12/24/04 and 12/29/04 and loved it. I was a bit wary given some of the negative reviews but I think some of the complaints are clearly unfounded--for example--the construction across the street was no more than a new building going up in this part of Miami where there has been an explosion of new constrction and in no way interfered with the great views. Yes the pool is in another area of the hotel, but this is true in many hotels. The Conrad is a very cool and New York-sylish hotel-urbane and sophisticated. The rooms were spacious and nicely furnished. We stayed in two different suites--a one bedroom within the hotel and a two bedroom suite/residence and both were really great spaces. The rooftop pool area, especially for a city hotel, was relaxing and subdued--in fact the entire hotel had the same quiet atmosphere. We ate breakfast every morning at the hotel restaurant where food and service were stellar (same for other meals and room service). I found the staff very helpful--in fact I can't recall a single no to any request we had--and we had quite a few given we were there with our 6 and 15 year old boys as well. Overall a great hotel experience--and looking forwrd to a return visit. 
